combined_text: The unsold inventory of Elon Musk's Tesla is so large, it is now visible from space: Reports indicate that there are nearly 50,000 Teslas sitting in parking lots across the USA alone  so many, they can be spotted from space. Using satellite imagery, sources like Sherwood News discovered Teslas Texas Gigafactory lots went from partially filled in late 2023 to overflowing by March 2024.  Additional storage locations, including vacant malls and parking lots, are also being filled to capacity. Tesla reported building 433,371 vehicles in the first quarter of 2024 but only selling 386,810, leaving tens of thousands of excess units.  This surplus reflects a slowing EV market and Teslas price cuts failing to entice buyers. Satellite images reveal hundreds of Teslas packed outside places like Chesterfield Mall in St. Louis and former retail spaces like Sears in Moreno Valley, California. While Tesla maintains optimism about reversing this inventory buildup, the growing visibility of its unsold vehicles raises questions about the long-term demand for its once-dominant brand. combined_text: Is Tesla (TSLA) a buy in today's stock market? The stock went from the most hated stock earlier in the year to now everyone's favorite stock, and here's whether or not I think the stock is a good buy for 2025.  So Tesla's stock is back at all time highs, and here's whether or not the stock is a good buy at today's prices. I first started talking about Tesla in July of this year when the stock was trading at a little under $200, and although I was quite bullish on the stock and thought the bottom was in, the comment section disagreed. And now that I'm going to call Tesla overvalued at today's prices, the comment section will once again disagree with me. But the business really hasn't changed much since July, despite the stock doubling in a little under six months, proving that once again in the short term, all that dictates stock prices is sentiment. And since Elon's involvement in the Trump elections, the stock has been doing really well. But as far as the business goes, the company's growth has dramatically slowed down this year to only 8% growth in the most recent quarter, which is part of the reason the stock has underperformed in the past few years. But now, as interest rates drop and investors have brushed off recession fears, analysts are expecting around 15 to 20% growth over the next five years, which seems achievable to me. But the stock trades at a forward PE of 129, so unless you're expecting Tesla to double their margins and grow revenue at 30% a year, the stock seems to be back in overvalued territory.

Why didn't I sell earlier? I should have sold at the client. But that's the problem with stock investing. Is that you do not have a crystal ball? Because in the beginning, things were like, wow, this is definitely going to be good for the stock markets. Remember what happened in 2016? Everything was great for the stock market. Like, the first Trump presidency really was good for the stock market. And so I just thought, I should hold, I should hold. Number one is you can't really beat the market. Like you can't time the market. I could sell right now and I could actually lose money because tomorrow it could go back up. Like that's the problem with the stock market. You can't predict what's going to really happen. There are certain indications. That's what market data showed on Tuesday. It means sales of the all-electric carmaker dropped for a second consecutive month, and that was despite rising overall EV registrations on the continent. The European Automobile Manufacturers Association showed Elon Musk's battery electric brand has sold just under 43% fewer cars in Europe so far this year. Tesla held 1.8% of the total market in February down from 2.8% last year. It sold fewer than 17,000 cars in the EU, Britain and European Free Trade Association countries compared to 28,000 in the same month last year. Tesla currently faces a number of challenges in Europe. The EV Maker has a smaller aging lineup. While traditional automaker rivals and new Chinese entrance launch often cheaper electric models. CEO Musk has also caused controversy by courting far-right parties in Europe which has hit Tesla sales. Overall the data showed battery electric sales in the same market to root more than a quarter against February last year, even as total car sales fell 3.1%. combined_text: The Tesla Model S review telsa models telsamodels highmiles elonmusk elon teslamotors nc chrisrayner fyp stitch due  I've had my high mileage 2014 Tesla Model S for about 4 months now and I'm gonna give you a quick breakdown of all the expenses so far. I put about 8,000 miles on this car in 4 months to equal about 2,000 miles per month and keep in mind I do have other cars that drive. My initial purchase price was $25,600 and this car came with a brand new battery and brand new motor. Well I do spend most of the time at superchargers that have spent about $31 in electricity so far this month. Beginning of the year I really haven't spent too much more out of $140 at a pocket total. It is worth noting that I do have the free supercharging package on this model. Now unfortunately I have had some issues with the car so far and my auxiliary battery went out and that's pretty much been the only thing other than the window regulator. As you can see I've had Tesla service come out a couple times that most recent one was canceled because I ended up fixing myself. Fortunately it's not actually that expensive it's totaled about $281 for those two trips. Just after purchasing it I was on my way to Wilmington and I blew out a tire so I put two new tires in the back and believed that told it right around $320 or so. Overall I've got a love hey relationship with the car. I do really like how it looks it's very sleek all my friends love it. It looks really good when I'm showing houses but when I don't charge it or plug it in overnight it's really annoying having to sit at the supercharger for an hour to get it fully charged. Definitely got its pros and cons not upset I bought it but I'll probably rock it for a few more months and start looking for a newer model 3 or Model X. Or who knows maybe the Tesla truck will be up by then. So no major regrets this far I definitely love Teslas and I definitely recommend Buy One just maybe look for somebody with less miles.

combined_text: Le Tesla Model Pi, un smartphone rumeur de Tesla et Elon Musk, pourrait sortir en 2024, bien que cela ne soit pas confirm. Il aurait un prix estim entre 800 et 2000 dollars, une batterie de 4700 mAh, jusqu 12 Go de RAM et 512 Go de stockage. Parmi ses fonctionnalits uniques, on parle de connexion via Starlink pour un rseau mondial, recharge solaire et commande par Neuralink. Il pourrait aussi permettre le minage de cryptomonnaies comme le Marscoin. https:www.tomsguide.frtelephone-tesla-pi-5g-fiche-technique-prix https:lekki.frtelephone-tesla-pi-2022-5g-premier-apercu-prix-et-date-de-sortie  Les stétiques du Tesla Model P est un chez d'oeuvre, avec un revêtement extérieur changeant de couleurs toutes les 30 minutes en fonction de la lumière ambiante. Cette transformation est particulièrement saisissante lorsqu'elle est exposée au soleil. A noter que le designer en chef de Tesla, Antenio Deroza, ancien membre de l'équipe iPhone Apple a rapporté au téléphone Tesla, un design élégant et raffiné. Elon Musk a certainement réuni une équipe de première ordre pour créer un téléphone au design élégant, au téléphone Tesla. Au-delà de son esthétique, la caractéristique exceptionnelle et la technologie neuraligne, établissant une connexion directe entre le cerveau de l'utilisateur ou le téléphone pour des commandes infutives. Cette innovation présente un potentiel considérable, un particulier pour les personnes ayant des troubles de la parole, au front à moyen de communication novateur. De plus, elle pourrait avoir des applications en matière de diagnostic médicale, permettant de médecin de comprendre l'activité cérébrale partagée entre les patients et d'explorer de nouvelles voies de traitement. Elon Musk envisage un avenir où cette technologie contribuera à guérir les maladies neurologiques et révolutionnera les messages textuelles et vaut-aux. L'impact de cette technologie sur la société est remarquable. Si vous êtes intrigué, envisagez-nous abonner à la chaîne. Pour le monde interconnecté d'aujourd'hui, l'accès internet fiable et rapide est essentielle, mais les régions éloignées ont souvent du mal à l'obtenir. Le modèle Tesla PIE relève ce défi en intégrant le WIFI, assurant une connectivité internet constante. De plus, il dépasse les réseaux cellulaires, intégrant une connectivité satellites via les satellites Tharaliques de SpaceX, en front des vitesses de téléchargement, à l'an jusqu'à 200 mégabits par seconde. Cette technologie révolutionnaire est déjà utilisée dans le monde entier, y compris dans des régions éloignées comme Alaska. L'objectif ambitieux d'Elon Musk est de fournir un accès internet ultra rapide, à l'ensemble de l'Afrique, si la fin de 2022, c'est comme l'or ainsi le faussé numérique et améliorant l'éducation, des santé et la communication. À l'air numérique actuelle, la sécurité et la confidentialité revêtent une importance primordiale et l'utilité Tesla modèle PIE excellne dans ces deux domaines. Ce smartphone offre des fonctionnalités de chiffrement de pointe, garantissant une protection maximale de vos informations personnelles. Tesla a accord d'une priorité absolue à la vie privée de l'utilisateur, assurant la confidentialité de vos discussions appelées de des personnels. En plus d'un chiffrement robuste, le smartphone Tesla intègre des mesures de sécurité de pointe pour contrecarrer les pirates informatiques et les accès non-autorisés, des moyens de langagement envers la confidentialité et la sécurité des utilisateurs. Cela se distingue de l'iPhone qui peut être vulnérables au piratage lorsqu'il est connecté à des réseaux wifi publics. Des entreprises peuvent avoir confiance dans la sécurité de leurs données sensibles. De plus, la technologie inovante Starlink d'Elon Musk chez SpaceX pourrait potentiellement faire du Tesla Model P, le premier téléphone par satellite accessible au consommateur. En exploitant le service Internet Autofitèse de Starlink, le téléphone Tesla offre une connectivité sans précédent ou même dans des emplois reculés. La technologie Starlink a déjà un impact mondial avec les efforts d'Elon Musk visant à étendre l'accès internet ultra-rapie dans l'Afrique bien avancée. Cette extension de l'accès Internet promet des avancés dans l'éducation, des soins de santé et la communication dans des zones rurales. L'approche unique de Tesla en matière de production, distingue davantage l'entreprise. Contrairement à Apple qui se procure de nombreux composants à l'extérieur pour ces smartphones, Tesla conserve à contrôle significatif sur son processus de production. La réputation de Tesla en matière de fabrication de tous les composants de ses voitures, s'étend à ces smartphones. Cependant, ce niveau de contrôle et d'interpendance s'accompagne de ses propres défis. Et en donné la complexité de la fabrication endomicile, il est probable que le Tesla modèle PIS soit produit légèrement plus lentement que l'iPhone d'Apple. Cependant, l'engagement de Tesla envers la qualité et l'innovation reste inébranlable, à l'agré des ventuels retardes. Dauté de fonctionnalité de pointe et de capacités futuristes, le Tesla modèle PIS promet de révolutionner l'industrie des smartphones. Ce téléphone est véritablement révolutionnaire en raison de sa grande capacité de stockage, de sa vitesse de traitement impressionnante, de son appareil photo de haut de qualité et de son exceptionnel autonomie. De plus, l'intégration de la technologie neuralique nous vous vit fiers intégrés et de la connectivité satellites ouvre de passionnante nouvelle possibilité en matière de connectivité internet et de communication. Le téléphone Tesla m'el accent sur la sécurité et la confidentialité garantissant la protection des informations personnelles.

combined_text: MY DREAM CAR TESLA MODEL X SEVEN SEATS GOD DO YOUR MIRACLES   Three reasons the Tesla Model X is the perfect family SUV. The Tesla Model X has Falcon Wing doors that open upwards, making it a lot easier for your passengers to get inside. And once you're inside to close the Falcon Wing doors, all you have to do is press the close button on the B pillar, similar to a minivan and the door will shut automatically for you. Next, the Tesla Model X can be configured with up to seven seats. And while the legroom in the third row does look a little tight at first glance, that can be adjusted by pulling on this lever to pull the second row forward. But honestly, the third row is probably most comfortable for little kids. And finally, the Model X has a 9.4-inch rear display, which is mainly used for controlling the airflow for the second row. But it can also be used to adjust the front passenger seat. That way, if you need more legroom, you can do it without getting out of the car. You can also control the music that's playing in the car, watch TV movies and YouTube, or even play games on the rear display. And it's also really nice that you can pair Bluetooth headphones or controllers to the rear display. And of course, below the rear display, you'll find two pop-out cup holders and two USB-C ports.
